This set the stage for Wednesday's agreement to remove the rest of the material - according to an official employee, who remains anonymous due to the sensitivity of the topic, about 500 pounds.
The deal appears to be one of the most important outcomes of Obama’s “Nuclear Security Summit of the 47 Nations” in April, which ruled out Belarus.
